  "response": "For a healthy 34-year-old male, the most important vitamins and supplements generally include:\n\n1. Multivitamin\n- Provides a comprehensive mix of essential vitamins and minerals\n- Helps fill nutritional gaps in diet\n\n2. Vitamin D\n- Supports bone health\n- Boosts immune system\n- Helps with muscle function\n- Especially important if you have limited sun exposure\n\n3. Vitamin B Complex\n- Supports energy metabolism\n- Promotes brain function\n- Helps maintain healthy nervous system\n- Includes B12, B6, and folate\n\n4. Omega-3 Fatty Acids\n- Supports heart and brain health\n- Reduces inflammation\n- Promotes joint health\n\n5. Magnesium\n- Supports muscle and nerve function\n- Helps regulate blood pressure\n- Aids in sleep quality\n\n6. Vitamin C\n- Boosts immune system\n- Supports collagen production\n- Acts as an antioxidant\n\n7. Zinc\n- Supports immune function\n- Promotes testosterone production\n- Aids in wound healing\n\nNote: Always consult with a healthcare professional before starting any supplement regimen, as individual needs can vary based on diet, health conditions, and lifestyle.",
